title: CROSS COUNTRY: Kingwood girls take second at McNeil Cross Country Invitational
text:
Previous Next Kingwood girls take second at McNeil Cross Country Invitational 
Mustang Erin Gallagher competes at the McNeil Invitational on Saturday. The Mustangs took second in the 42 team field. Advertisement Posted: Sunday, October 4, 2015 10:00 am CROSS COUNTRY: Kingwood girls take second at McNeil Cross Country Invitational By Community Report Houston Community Newspapers 
The Kingwood girls cross country team traveled to Round Rock on Saturday for the McNeil Invitational. The meet is held each year at Old Settlers Park, the site of the UIL State Cross Country Championship in November. 
The meet featured 42 teams in the gold division and was a showdown between the top three teams from the 2014 UIL 6A state meet: Hebron, Marcus, and Kingwood. 
When the dust settled, Marcus took home the title with 73 points followed by Kingwood (107), Smithson Valley (117), Hebron (162), and Katy (248). 
Mustang senior Abby Guidry paced Kingwood with a fourth place finish, covering the 5K course in a time of 17:22. Also scoring for Kingwood were senior Erin Gallagher (8th, 17:37), senior Olivia Thompson (18th 18:08), freshman McKenzie Clark (31st, 18:27), and sophomore Jessica Hergott (54th, 18:46). 
Also running at McNeil for the Mustangs were senior Jasmine Amo (65th, 18:52), junior Sarah Antrich (67th, 18:53), sophomore Megan Eichler (90th, 19:14), senior Kayla Russell (120th, 19:34), and junior Kendall VanNatter (123rd, 19:35). 
Next up for the Mustangs is the UIL District 16-6A Championship at College Park High School on October 15.
